Ordered their Forager Burger ($12.90) with a side of pulled beef fries (additional $2).

The burger patty was not grilled, it tasted rather disgusting like it was steamed. There was a weird aftertaste from the patty as well.

The pulled beef fries tasted decent, but the beef was slightly tough and the amount of meat on the fries was very little.

Would not recommend this particular meal combo.

Purchase Pasta üçù for Takeaway. Food tastes Nice, Just that the portion of the pasta is small and little or did they accidentally swap the portion side with the meat side? üòÇüòÅ We're hoping to see more improve on the takeaway portion area perhaps.

New stall at bukit batok's new hawker centre. Extremely affordable western food options. Portions are huge and food was amazing.

I ordered their ribeye set and samyang pasta and definitely was not disappointed. The beef was cooked well and dishes were flavourful.

Definitely worth trying if you are there.
